org.rendersnake.internal

Class StackedMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rendersnake.internal.StackedMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<String,Object>

    public class StackedMap
extends Object
implements Map<String,Object>
    A nested hash-based Map implementation. If an entry is not found in the map at nesting level N then retry in map N-1, if N >= 0; return null otherwise.
    Author:
    ernestmicklei

      • StackedMap

        public StackedMap()
        Constructs an empty StackedMap.

      • StackedMap

        public StackedMap(Map<? extends String,? extends Object> m)
        Constructs a new StackedMap with the same mappings as the specified Map. The mappings will be created at depth 0.
        Parameters:
        m - the Map whose mappings are to be placed in this Map, cannot be null.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if m == null.

    • Method Detail

      • push

        public void push()
        Increases the depth of the stack of maps. From now on all put(String,Object) operations will store the mappings at the higher depth.

        Note that pop() will make all mappings at the current depth unavailable.

      • pop

        public void pop()
        Decreases the depth of the stack of maps, effectively removing all mappings at the current level. From now on all put(String,Object) operations will store the mappings at the lower depth.

        Note that push() will create a higher depth.

        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if getDepth() == 0.

      • getDepth

        public int getDepth()
        Returns the depth of the stack.
        Returns:
        the depth of the stack, always >= 0.
